This occurs in both the latest nightly and release.

For-loops with a particular condition and arrangement of spaces cause the coloring to break from that point onward. Example code is below and attached screenshot - the last loop breaks.

The format has to be:
- Less then symbol
- No spaces
- Variable (foo, foo.bar. foo['bar'] is okay)
- One or more spaces
- ; character

If you change any one of those, as in the example below, the colouring is fine. It's almost as though it's seeing what looks like the start of an HTML tag and getting confused.

``` javascript
for (var i = 0; i <400; i++) { // Start loop
    doSomething();
}

for (var i = 0; i < foo ; i++) { // Start loop
    doSomething();
}

for (var i = 0; i < foo; i++) { // Start loop
    doSomething();
}

for (var i = 0; i <foo; i++) { // Start loop
    doSomething();
}

for (var i = 0; i <foo ; i++) { // Start loop
    doSomething();
}
```

